# SF Docs MCP — Development Rules

## Architecture
- `help.salesforce.com` extraction uses the Aura API via native `fetch()` — NO Playwright
- `developer.salesforce.com` extraction uses Playwright with stealth plugin
- All extractors implement the `Extractor` interface from `src/types.ts`
- Cache layer is SQLite via `better-sqlite3` with 24-hour TTL

## Key Files
- `src/extractors/help-sf.ts` — Most critical file. Aura API integration.
- `src/extractors/developer-sf.ts` — Playwright-based extraction.
- `src/extractors/index.ts` — URL routing and cache integration.
- `src/mcp-server.ts` — MCP tool definitions. Thin wiring only.

## Testing
Always verify changes with:
```bash
npm run test-url -- "https://help.salesforce.com/s/articleView?id=ind.psc_admin_concept_psc_welcom.htm&type=5"
```

## Important
- The `fwuid` rotates ~3x/year. The extractor self-heals by scraping the homepage.
- `aura.token` is always `null` for public articles.
- `release: ""` fetches the latest version.
- Never introduce browser automation for help.salesforce.com — Salesforce Locker Service detects CDP.
